						               													<description>ImpeRunde is a tremendous wooden board game for 3-6 players. The colonial powers of the 18th century struggle for the control of the sea routes and influence in the colonies. If possible, they try to reach their goals in peace. But when diplomacy fails, conflict threatens. Excitement and interaction captivate the players for 3 to 8 hours. The game board with 80 cm in diameter, over 1.000 meeples and the game box are made of wood, the cotton bags are fairtrade! &amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Imperunde each player assumes the role of an eighteenth-century colony power. The goal of the game is, to be the first to set up a fixed number of trading posts and to have no debts as a colonial power. The count of trading posts is recommended by the rules according to the desired game length and number of players, but can be adjusted by the players. During the game, players must build new colonies, manage their national budgets, strategically shift armies, conduct diplomatic negotiations on war and peace, conquer other colonies, defend their own colonies, and plan and conduct their intelligence activity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
